Thanks for the reply! I think that the best option to work with Nertea is to have a option to make them work like stock tanks, with <abbr title="Liquid Fuel">LF</abbr>/Ox, so it can applies it's own system, with the cooling. But I'm no expert.  

I did a test install without firespitter (by accident), and got this:  
![2DpIJQ1.png](https://i.imgur.com/2DpIJQ1.png)  

The wings simple got the resources and Nertea's fuel switch took over, like any other tank.  

Since many mods I use have Firespitter as a dependence, I need to keep it. So I tried to remove everything in GameData\OPT\mm\_config, the wings lost all the tanks.  

Them I removed only the OPT\_FS.cfg, no effect. Removed OPT\_Resource\_Defaults only, lost the tanks.  

Them I removed OPT\_FS.cfg, and removed the mod dependencies (:NEEDS[!Firespitter,!RealFuels,!ModularFuelTanks]) from OPT\_Resource\_Defaults.cfg, so it should always applies the tanks. It worked for all tanks, wings and cabins, with firespitter installed. But I lost the custom OPT category ![:huh:](//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_undecided.gif ":huh:") I don't see any relation for this to happen.  

